ir 0.1.0 — self-describing R scripts

USAGE:
    ir run [Rscript-options...] [--with <pkg>]... [--r-version <spec>] <script.R> [args...]
    ir run [Rscript-options...] [--with <pkg>]... [--r-version <spec>] -e <expr> [args...]
    ir cache <command>

`ir run` reads the YAML frontmatter from <script.R>, resolves its
dependencies, builds a dedicated package library, and runs the script
against it. With -e it evaluates inline R expressions instead of a file,
--with adds dependencies on the command line, and --r-version selects
the R version with rig. Leading Rscript options are passed to Rscript for
the user-code phase; trailing args are passed through to the program.
`ir cache` manages the dependency resolution and materialised library cache.

ENVIRONMENT:
    IR_CACHE_DIR   override the cache dir (default: tools::R_user_dir("ir", "cache"))
    IR_RSCRIPT     path to the Rscript executable (default: Rscript on PATH)
